Amanda Ripley, author of "The 
Smartest Kids in the World," says kids need "rigorous" education
to survive in a changing economy. Ripley talks with Bloomberg's 
 Tom Keene  and Sara Eisen on Bloomberg Radio's "Bloomberg 
Surveillance."     (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 06:17
 